m international renown, culminating in his receipt of the 1905 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Literature\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Literature\">Nobel Prize in Literature<\/a> for his \"outstanding merits as an epic writer.\"<\/p><p>Many of his novels remain in print. In Poland he is best known for his \"<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Trilogy\" title=\"The Trilogy\">Trilogy<\/a>\" of historical novels \u2013 <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/With_Fire_and_Sword\" title=\"With Fire and Sword\">With Fire and Sword<\/a><\/i>, <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Deluge_(novel)\" title=\"The Deluge (novel)\">The Deluge<\/a><\/i>, and <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fire_in_the_Steppe\" title=\"Fire in the Steppe\">Fire in the Steppe<\/a><\/i> \u2013 set in the 17th-century <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Polish-Lithuanian_Commonwealth\" title=\"Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth<\/a>; internationally he is best known for <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quo_Vadis_(novel)\" title=\"Quo Vadis (novel)\">Quo Vadis<\/a><\/i>, set in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nero\" title=\"Nero\">Nero<\/a>'s <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ancient_Rome\" title=\"Ancient Rome\">Rome<\/a>. <i>The Trilogy<\/i> and <i>Quo Vadis<\/i> have been filmed, the latter several times, with Hollywood's <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quo_Vadis_(1951_film)\" title=\"Quo Vadis (1951 film)\">1951 version<\/a> receiving the most international recognition.<\/p>","name":"Henryk Sienkiewicz","place_of_birth":"Wola Okrzejska, Congress Poland","place_of_death":"Vevey, Switzerland","text":"Henryk Sienkiewicz ,  born in partitioned Poland (Russian Empire) , Literature, 1905","year":1905.0}